# Force LF for all air-ts sources and fixtures. The parity tests read fixture
# JSON and the golden corpus and compare byte-for-byte; a stray CR from Windows
# autocrlf would corrupt those comparisons. Linux CI must see exactly what was
# committed. (The corpus itself is already pinned to LF by the repo-root
# .gitattributes; this covers the package's own files.)
* text=auto eol=lf
